      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution) must be directly relevant to the device safety decision.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index and volumetric shear stress exposure are the primary QoIs. Both are directly linked to red blood cell damage mechanisms relevant to CPB device safety evaluation per FDA guidance."
